# Cursor rules — read the project index first

Before exploring or grepping this repository, read `PROJECT_INDEX.md` at the repo
root. It is a generated, tool-neutral map — overview, architecture, per-subsystem
key files, run/test commands, and known gotchas — produced so any coding agent can
understand the repo WITHOUT re-scanning it. Prefer reading the index over walking
the tree: it saves tokens and surfaces footguns documented per subsystem.

The index's bottom "Structure" block is auto-generated by `tools/index_refresh.py`
(deterministic, no AI). Do not hand-edit between the AUTO-INDEX markers. After large
structural changes, rebuild the semantic sections with the `project-index` workflow.

Project-specific Claude guidance lives in `CLAUDE.md`. Always honor it.
